‚Å†
"Slightly ashamed to admit how many bites I ate trying to get the bite shot ü•∫üòÇ‚Å†
-‚Å†
& the best part is they can be whatever you want them to be! If you‚Äôre nut free, use whatever seed butter you like, If you do like nuts, use whatever nut butter you like! Don‚Äôt do white chocolate? Use regular! These babies do it alllll friends üòç‚Å†
-‚Å†
‚Ä¢base:‚Å†
1/3 cup protein powder or almond flour (I used @macr0mike cookie dough)‚Å†
3 Tbsp coconut flour‚Å†
2 tsp vanilla‚Å†
1/4 cup maple syrup‚Å†
1/2 tsp sea salt‚Å†
1/4 cup runny nut/seed butter (I used @georgiagrinders cashew but use seed butter to keep these nut free)‚Å†
1-3 tsp plant milk, as needed‚Å†
‚Ä¢cheesecake‚Å†
1/2 cup vegan cream cheese (I use @miyokoscreamery because I like the ingredients best)‚Å†
1/4 cup @culinayogurt yogurt (or yogurt of choice)‚Å†
1/2 tsp vanilla‚Å†
3-4 tbsp maple syrup‚Å†
‚Ä¢ganache:‚Å†
1/2 cup white chocolate chips‚Å†
2 tbsp nut/seed butter‚Å†
3 tbsp coconut cream‚Å†
-‚Å†
Combine all base ingredients until dough forms. Press into the bottom of a lined loaf pan. Different proteins yield different results so add some plant milk if needed to reach desired consistency.‚Å†
To make the cheesecake, whisk everything together until completely smooth. Taste & adjust flavors as needed, if you like it sweeter add more maple! Spread over base.‚Å†
Melt the ganache ingredients together until completely smooth. Pour over the top. Place in freezer to set. Cut into cubes & enjoy!"‚Å†
