While #intuitiveeating is all about connecting with your internal signals, it can be really hard to over ride the narrative in your brain that's saying "but you just ate, you can't possibly be hungry"üôç‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è‚Å†
‚Å†
How can we defend ourselves against the food industry and it's hyper-palatable food?üçî üç©‚Å†
‚Å†
By being adequately nourished.‚Å†
‚Å†
How can we stop eating our way through the afternoon lull?üç™‚Å†
‚Å†
By being adequately nourished.‚Å†
‚Å†
How can we feel in control of our food choices?üëä‚Å†
‚Å†
Yep, you guessed it. By being adequately nourished.‚Å†
‚Å†
Under-eating, and yes, 1200-1500 calories a day is UNDER eating, leaves you in a biological state that will keep your focus on food and craving calorie dense food. That's not will power issues, that's biology.‚Å†
‚Å†
And yet, the diet/wellness industry has taught us to believe that our biology is a character flaw.‚Å†
‚Å†
The best way to deal with over eating is to stop under eating.‚Å†
‚Å†
**to be clear, I don't have anything against hyper palatable foods. I enjoy them on the regular. My point is simply that I choose them sanely now instead of feeling triggered by TV ads or billboards on my way home. ‚Å†
